<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The term =E2=80=9Chedge fund=E2=80=9D can refe=
r to both (1) a small firm run by a single idiosyncratic genius with a gut =
instinct and a tiny pirate crew or (2) a gigantic institution that is in th=
e business of identifying talented investors=C2=A0and <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30618705.287441/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlZGl=
mZi5jby9hcmNoaXZlL3BvZC1wZW9wbGUv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBba398e74" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
"> systematically extracting alpha from them</a>. At some point a lot of th=
e former category transition into the latter category, and it can be awkwar=
d. If you started a hedge fund, and your firm grew into a financial service=
s behemoth with thousands of employees and tens of billions of dollars unde=
r management, and you=E2=80=99re now at retirement age, the tension is:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">On the one hand, it is very important =
to transition your firm into an institution that can work without you: You =
owe it to your employees and to your clients to make sure that the firm wil=
l thrive after you leave; plus, you probably own a bunch of shares and woul=
d like them to continue to be valuable.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: =
5px;">On the other hand it is your firm, created in your image, and these o=
ther people don=E2=80=99t have your creative genius and are going to mess i=
t up.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I enjoyed <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/30618705.287441/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMy=
8wMi8yMC9idXNpbmVzcy9icmlkZ2V3YXRlci1yYXktZGFsaW8tcmV0aXJlLmh0bWw/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cB24742edd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> this New York Times article</a> about ho=
w Ray Dalio, who has spent the last decade or so pretending to retire from =
Bridgewater Associates,<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-9" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; =
background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[9]</span>
</a>=C2=A0apparently did his most recent retirement=C2=A0by going door to d=
oor asking all of his employees for cash to get him to leave:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But Mr. Dalio wasted little time in telling co=
lleagues that he was not interested in a simple passing of the baton, accor=
ding to current and former employees. He approached dozens of top employees=
 =E2=80=94 at the time, Bridgewater had roughly 1,500 full-time staff membe=
rs =E2=80=94 and told them they would have to buy his shares with their own=
 money, some of those employees said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Dalio offered to arrange 10-year loans to =
those who lacked the funds to buy him out, according to two former employee=
s. If they declined, he intimated that they should consider leaving the fir=
m, they said. Still, even as he sold shares to his colleagues, decreasing h=
is ownership, his founder shares kept him in control.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the one hand, that is not really how big in=
stitutional financial firms operate; Goldman Sachs Group Inc. did not take =
up a collection to get Lloyd Blankfein to quit. On the other hand, while Br=
idgewater=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>a big institutional financial firm, it is a=
lso an extension of Ray Dalio, and you can see why it=E2=80=99s hard for hi=
m to let go. =E2=80=9CAt an internal meeting last year during the heat of t=
he exit negotiations, Mr. Dalio described the hedge fund as his =E2=80=98pr=
operty rights,=E2=80=99 according to one employee, and indicated that he ex=
pected to be compensated accordingly.=E2=80=9D I mean, fair.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway for now there are non-Dalio=C2=A0<a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30618705.287441/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuYnJpZGdld2F0ZXIuY29tL3Blb3BsZS9icmlkZ2V3YXRlcnMtbmV3LWxlYWRlcnNoaXA=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc614e145" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> co-chief executive officers</a=
>, Nir Bar Dea and Mark Bertolini, and I guess they are remaking it in thei=
r image?</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the meantime, Mr. Bar Dea has begun dismant=
ling some parts of Mr. Dalio=E2=80=99s legacy. Bridgewater dropped many of =
his =E2=80=9CPrinciples,=E2=80=9D and their associated ratings tools. Givin=
g unvarnished feedback to one another =E2=80=94 a stalwart of Mr. Dalio=E2=
=80=99s =E2=80=9Cradical transparency=E2=80=9D=E2=80=94 is now optional, cu=
rrent employees said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still, some of Mr. Bar Dea=E2=80=99s changes h=
ave a hint of the hedge fund=E2=80=99s old ways. He has recently taken to t=
elling employees that he is coming up with his own list of =E2=80=9CPrincip=
les.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What? Surely that=E2=80=99s the fastest way to=
 get Dalio to un-retire again. Never mind the money; if you scrap Dalio=E2=
=80=99s Principles and replace them with your own Principles and they are d=
ifferent principles =E2=80=94=C2=A0if you replace radical transparency with=
 radical politeness? =E2=80=94=C2=A0then he=E2=80=99s going to be on you li=
ke a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30618705.2874=
41/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY25iYy5jb20vMjAxMS8wMy8wMy90aGUtd2VpcmQtd29ybGQtb2YtcmF5=
LWRhbGlvcy1icmlkZ2V3YXRlci1oZWRnZS1mdW5kLmh0bWw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8d=
89b7a5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;"> hyena on a wildebeest</a>.</p>
